The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                              NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Kanpur, Feb. 8 (PTI): Police will give their mobile numbers to schoolgirls to check the growing number of eve-teasing cases.           
	The decision was taken at a meeting of city police officers and school principals yesterday. The heads of schools have been asked to dispense those numbers to every single girl so that officers can be contacted at the time of the incident, a source said. In addition, plain-clothed policewomen will be stationed outside girls schools.                   
	Akola (PTI): Three debt-ridden farmers committed suicide in Maharashtras Akola and Buldana districts on Thursday. Mahadeo Ukardaji and Ramesh Shankar hanged themselves while Mahadeo Sitaram Bhagwat consumed poison.                   
	Mumbai (PTI): Friday was perhaps Mumbais coldest day since 1962 with the minimum temperature at 8.5C. The mercury was at 7.4C in the city on January 27, 1962. A western disturbance in north India influenced the weather in the city.                   
	Sonepat (PTI): The special checking staff of Northern Railways hauled up 227 passengers at a station for travelling without tickets on Friday. A fine was imposed on the defaulters. Six of them, who failed to pay the penalty, were sent to Ambala jail.                  
	Sonepat (PTI): Police arrested four persons on Thursday night for smuggling bulls into Uttar Pradesh. Twenty-one bulls were seized from them, Acharya Om Sarup Arya, the president of the Haryana State Gaushala Sangh, said.                   
	 Jaipur (PTI): Two passengers were killed and 12 injured when their bus collided with a truck near Chak Dhani village in Nagaur. The dead were identified as Asraf and Shankar Lal.                                                                                                                           
